^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|West has a pretty good hand once East opens 1S. Using Bergen's hand evaluation, it is close to 10 points. So, one could consider this a limit raise with three card support, and bid 3S. But, there are some negatives to the hand. The unprotected Jacks are a minus and an eight card fit is not nearly as good as a nine card fit. If I change South's hand to KQJX Jxxx x Jxxx, I would probably make a limit raise, due to the fourth trump. The difference between a 9 card fit and 8 card fit is huge.|
