^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|East has an interesting choice. East wants to compete to at least 3S. Given all of East's Aces and 2 good suits (clubs and spades), there is a small possibility that their side has 4S. Most experts play 3S here directly is just competing. In other words, they don't want to give South  a chance to bid. Therefore, East must make another bid to show a good hand. 3C or redouble are both fine here.|
