^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|South  does not really want to give North a choice of what suit to play and   should bid 3D to show her best suit. This does not show extra points, merely a preference for where to play. It is similar to when the auction goes 1x-dbl-rdbl. A bid by the responder to the takeout double does not show extra values. On that auction, the first bidders have good hands and, therefore, the responder to the takeout doubler cannot possibly have a good hand. The same principle applies here. 3D is merely preference for a suit, it does not show any values.|
