^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|North could have as many as 17 points. To jump shift North needs 18 points. Therefore, South, with 10 Bergen's Starting Points, should not consider passing. 1N is a possible bid,  but the club stopper is iffy. If North has longish diamonds, since North also has long spades, it is likely North could be short in clubs. Therefore, although 1N is a possible bid, it has two flaws.|
