^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|From North's point of view, 2D really improved his hand. It tended to deny clubs, because with clubs South might very well bid NT. So, North's singleton club looks useful. Additionally, South  could easily have five hearts in which case 4H must have plays. Finally, with 15 HCP and a singleton, North, who has already denied 18 points, should show a good hand. 2H would be too weak. |
