NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, because West has the Ace of hearts, it is likely that West can arrange at least one diamond ruff for East, and possibly two. So, the Ace of hearts, Ace of clubs, and two ruffs will set the hand. Then, an expert West would lead a diamond. BTW, a slightly less expert West would lead A of hearts and a heart because it sounds like North is short of clubs and you want to cut down on club ruffs. If you chose the Ace of hearts, I would not fault you.|
